.TH NEXUS-KEY 1 "November 2025" "Nexus CLI 0.11.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nexus-key \- API key management commands for Nexus
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nexus key
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
API key management commands for Nexus graph database.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B list
List all API keys in the system.
.TP
.B create \fINAME\fR
Create a new API key with the specified name.
.TP
.B get \fIID\fR
Get information about a specific API key.
.TP
.B revoke \fIID\fR
Revoke an API key.
.SH OPTIONS FOR CREATE
.TP
.BR \-\-permissions " " \fIPERMS\fR
Comma-separated list of permissions to grant.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List all API keys:
.B nexus key list
.TP
Create a new API key:
.B nexus key create mykey --permissions read,write
.TP
Get key info:
.B nexus key get abc123
.TP
Revoke a key:
.B nexus key revoke abc123
.SH SECURITY
.IP \(bu 2
API keys are shown only once when created - save them securely.
.IP \(bu 2
Use environment variables or config files instead of command-line arguments for keys.
.IP \(bu 2
Revoke unused keys promptly.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nexus (1),
.BR nexus-user (1)
